news.title: Sovereign wealth fund buys 25% stake in London's Mayfair district
news.para: The 2.3 million square feet portfolio is predominately office and retail assets clustered around Grosvenor Street and Mount Street, the fund said in a statement.

news.title: NDR InvIT acquires industrial and warehousing portfolio for Rs 706.1 crore
news.para: The deal is expected to deliver robust returns and includes properties with 100 per cent occupancy, marquee tenants, and a weighted average lease expiry (WALE) of 15.4 years, NDR InvIT said.

news.title: Pune civic body demands 15 govt land parcels for key projects
news.para: Govt land falls under the jurisdiction of the district collector and PMC needs to submit a proposal of the development work to the office.

news.title: Landowners of BDA's town planning schemes worry over land conversion delays
news.para: The matter was discussed during a meeting between BDA officials and landowners, covering TP scheme no. 8, which includes Dasapur and Andharua mouzas on the outskirts here.

news.title: Mohali development body demolishes illegal structures in Nayagaon
news.para: The demolition drive was organised in two illegal colonies at Karoran village, Majri tehsil, near Nayagaon. Around 30 to 40 structures were razed during the operation.

news.title: Sunac China lands first onshore debt reduction in troubled property sector
news.para: The landmark deal enables Sunac, once one of China's largest real estate developers, to deleverage its 15.4 billion yuan ($2.11 billion) outstanding onshore debt by more than half.

news.title: Home prices in New Zealand dip as buyers wait for lower rates
news.para: Seasonally adjusted median house prices fell 1.0% in December versus the previous month, and 1.8% from the previous year.

news.title: GuocoLand and JV secure land for $496 million in Singapore
news.para: The consortium plans to develop the land into a mixed-use hub, with commercial operations and about 860 residential units above, according to the company's statement.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA to review its master plan 2041
news.para: The plan delineated and designated the VMRDA area into various policy zones, reflecting their growth opportunities and interventions to guide future investments in infrastructure and services.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 1,795 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: ​​In the South-West Zone, 189 properties were sealed while proceedings to seize 15 properties were initiated.

news.title: Chennai metro rail yet to begin work on Trichy metro proposal
news.para: While the DFR, submitted in August 2023, confirmed the viability of a metro system in Trichy, the project has not been prioritised by the state government.

news.title: Hebbal metro corridor faces delays due to unresolved land acquisition issues
news.para: The Karnataka Industrial Areas Development Board (KIADB) is yet to transfer 55 acres of land in Amanikere village to Bangalore Metro Rail Corporation Limited (BMRCL)

news.title: Dharwad HC orders Koppal civic body to approve khata transfer and building permits
news.para: The municipal commissioner presented govt circulars dated Mar 22, 2017, and Jan 5, 2018, stating properties without proper planning authority permissions were ineligible for khata issuance and could face legal action.

news.title: Cochin development body to launch residential, commercial projects soon
news.para: GCDA is planning to construct a twin tower on 80 cents land in Kadavanthra where the GCDA quarters stands. GCDA will demolish the existing two-storey building, built around 50 years ago, as they are presently in a dilapidated condition.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's commissioner sets Rs 350 crore tax recovery target for 2024-25
news.para: The tax department of the civic body has recently launched a major drive for recovering property taxes, especially targeting defaulters.

news.title: HC directs Goa PCB to frame green guidelines for ready-mix concrete plants
news.para: The board directed the plant to be immediately closed or operations suspended until it complies with the anti-pollution measures suggested by it.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to auction four properties with huge tax arrears
news.para: The two Dasarahalli properties had tax arrears of Rs 1.8 cr and Rs 30 lakh, respectively, while tax dues from Bommanahalli property was Rs 31 lakh and in east zone Rs 11 lakh.

news.title: Gurugram: Raheja Developers to face action for failing to deposit Rs 77 lakh for structural audit
news.para: Deputy commissioner Ajay Kumar has now recommended stringent measures, including halting the grant of future permissions to Raheja Developers, until the pending payments are made to ensure the compliance.

news.title: India Cements posts net profit of Rs 116.52 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Consolidated revenue from operations stood at Rs 940.81 crore in the third quarter as compared to Rs 1,113.06 crore in the year-ago period, the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Delhi: ED attaches assets worth Rs 82 crore in PMLA case against MGF Developments
news.para: The federal agency said in a statement that it was "pertinent to mention that Shravan Gupta is also an accused in the ED case of AgustaWestland helicopter scandal and has fled the country".
